      = South Africa<ref name=\"Mmakou 2015\">{{cite web |first=Boitumelo |last=Mmakou |title=Up Close & Personal With Nadia Nakai |website=Bona Magazine |date=2015-01-30 |url=http://www.bona.co.za/close-personal-nadia-nakai/ |access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n| genre            = [[Hip-Hop]]\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* [[Rapper]]\n* [[songwriter]]\n}}\n| instrument       = [[Vocals]]\n| years_active     = 2011-present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* Sid Records {{small|(former)}}\n* [[Family Tree Records|Family Tree]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Cassper Nyovest]]\n* [[Cleo Ice Queen]]\n* [[Gemini Major]]\n* Tshego\n* Miss Pru\n* Frank Casino \n* Priddy Ugly\n* [[Kwesta]]\n* [[Stefflon Don]]\n}}\n}}\n'''Nadia Nakai Kandava''' (born 18 May 1990) is a [[South Africa |South African]] rapper and songwriter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theindependent.co.zw/2017/06/23/nadia-rising-rap-queen/|title=Nakai: Rising rap queen|website=The Zimbabwe Independent}}</ref>\n\n==Early beginnings==\nNakai was born in South Africa.<ref name=\"Mmakou 2015\"/> Her father is South African and her mother is [[Zimbabwe|Zimbabwean]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peoplemagazine.co.za/celebrity-news/9-interesting-facts-about-nadia-nakai/|title=9 Interesting Facts About Nadia Nakai|website=People}}</ref> She studied Marketing, Communication, and Media Studies at [[Monash South Africa|Monash University]], [[Johannesburg]].<ref name=\"Mmakou 2015\"/>\n\n==Career==\n===2013\u20132016: Beginnings and ''Bragga''===\nNakai made her first television appearance on the [[e.tv]] hip hop show ''Shiz Niz'' where she won the Mixtape 101 competition, making her the first female to win the competition. She then rose to prominence in September 2013, when she released her debut single ''Like Me''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://soundcloud.com/sid-records/nadia-nakai-like-me|title=Nadia Nakai \"Like Me\" by Sid Records|website=SoundCloud}}</ref>. The following year, she was featured on the remix of [[Riky Rick]] song, ''Amantombazane'' amongst various acts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pltfrm.co.za/track-of-the-day-riky-rick-amantombazane-remix/|title=Track of the Day: Riky Rick - Amantombazane (Remix)|website=Platform}}</ref> As for June 2015, Nakai released her third single ''Saka Wena'' featuring rapper [[Ice Prince]], following her second single, ''Whatever'' featuring DotCom and Psyfo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/za/album/saka-wena-feat-ice-prince-single/971718993|title=Saka Wena (feat. Ice Prince) - Single by Nadia Nakai|website=Apple Music}}</ref>\n\nOn August 2016, Nakai pre-released her single ''The Man'' featuring [[Cassper Nyovest]] from her then upcoming [[extended play|EP]], ''Bragga''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sahiphopmag.co.za/2016/08/new-release-nadia-nakai-the-man-ft-cassper-nyovest/|title=New Release: Nadia Nakai - The Man [ft Cassper Nyovest]|website=SA Hip Hop Mag}}</ref> ''[[Bragga]]'' was then released on September 15, 2016. In November 2017, Nakai released her critically acclaimed single ''Naaa Meaan'' featuring Cassper Nyovest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timeslive.co.za/tshisa-life/tshisa-life/2017-11-02/-twitter-gives-nadia-nakais-new-track-a-thumbs-up/|title=Twitter gives Nadia Nakai's new track a thumbs up|website=TimesLive}}</ref> The song topped charts in several radio stations in South Africa. On November 4, 2016, she hosted the red carpet special for [[MTV Africa]] at the [[2018 MTV Europe Music Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sowetanlive.co.za/pic-of-the-day/2018-11-07-nadia-nakai-served-mzansi-sauce-at-the-mtv-emas/|title=Nadia Nakai served Mzansi sauce at the MTV EMAs|website=SowetanLIVE}}</ref>\n\n===2017\u2013present: ''Nadia Naked''===\nNakai is currently the co-host of [[MTV Base]] hip hop show, [[Yo! MTV Raps]] ''South Africa'' alongside television presenter Siyabonga Ngwekazi.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bona.co.za/nadia-nakai-and-siyabonga-ngwekazi-to-host-yo-mtv-raps-africa/|title=Nadia Nakai and Siyabonga Ngwekazi to host Yo! MTV Raps Africa|website=BONA}}</ref> On May 3, 2019, Nakai confirmed that her debut album ''Nadia Naked'' was released on June 28, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thesouthafrican.com/nadia-nakai-new-album-nadia-naked-release-date/|title=Nadia Nakai new album: 'Nadia Naked' gets a release date|website=The South African}}</ref> On May 18, 2019, \"Imma Boss\" was released as the lead single accompanied by the album's artwork cover.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.okayafrica.com/nadia-nakai-imma-boss-single/|title=Nadia Nakai Drops Quotable After Another In Her New Single 'Imma Boss'|website=OkayAfrica}}</ref>\n\n==Influences==\nNakai was inspired by a [[Kenya|Kenyan]] rapper, Nazizi, who she met while she was staying in Kenya. She said that Nazizi influenced her in starting her rapping career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.youthvillage.co.zw/2015/07/interview-with-african-rap-queen-nadia-nakai/|title=Interview With African Rap Queen Nadia Nakai|website=Youth Village Zimbabwe}}</ref>\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" | [[24th South African Music Awards]]\n|Naa Meaan (feat. [[Cassper Nyovest]])\n|Music Video Of The Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|}\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" | Zimbabwe Music Awards 2018\n|Herself\n|Artist Of The Year\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" | [[South African Hip Hop Awards 2019]]\n|Herself\n|Best Female\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|[[Nadia Naked]]\n|Album of the Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|Herself\n|MVP/Hustler Of The Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|}\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" | All African Music Awards 2019\n|[[Nadia Naked]]\n|Album Of The Year in Southern Africa\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|Imma Boss\n|Best Female Artiste in Southern Africa\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n|Herself\n|Best Artiste, Duo or Group in African Hip Hop\n|{{Won}}\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n===Studio Album===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ Studio album\n! Title\n! Extended play det